IncidentSuppNarrative.NarrativeText: On February 23, 2023, the Maryland State Police - Criminal Enforcement Division Eastern Region (CEDER) received a referral from the Talbot County Department of Social Services - Child Protective Services regarding an alleged sex offense. The initial complaint reported the following: The victim was identified as Michelle (hereinafter Michelle [O/F, DOB: 06/02/2011]), who is the daughter of James Arnaz Greene (hereinafter James [B/M, DOB: 07/03/1971]). Michelle was reported to have been residing with Susan Barklow (hereinafter Barklow [W/F, DOB: 03/12/1971]) and her grandsons to include the accused suspect, Steven Ronald Lee (hereinafter Steven [W/M, DOB: 05/22/2007]). The initial report alleged that Steven would enter Michelles bedroom and touch Michelles vagina and breasts. The report stated that Michelle had advised Susan of these allegations and the acts continued to happen. Since these events were alleged to have occurred, James and Michelle moved from Susans residence located at 9710 Tilghman Island Road, McDaniel, MD. The report was made to the Talbot County Department of Social Services who contacted the Maryland State Police - Criminal Enforcement Division Eastern Region (CEDER) for investigation. Michelle Greene Forenic Interview That same date at approximately 1200 hours, I, Corporal D. James confirmed that Michelle shared a bedroom with Michael and bedtime was between 9:00 pm and 11:00 pm. James was unable to provide any additional information trelevanto this investigation. Interview with Steven On April 18, 2023 at 1215 hours, Steven was interviewed at Saint Michaels High School. Steven denied ever entering Michelles bedroom or laying in bed with her. Steven did not know why Michelle would make these allegations. Steven stated that he was confused by this situation and did not have any information to provide relevant to this investigation.
